==Legacy==
He was the author of several textbooks and contributed to the ''Cambridge History of the British Empire''.<ref name="death"/>

Duncan McArthur Hall at Queen's University was named in his honour.<ref name="queens">{{cite web |url=http://www.queensu.ca/encyclopedia/m/mcarthurduncan.html |title=McArthur, Duncan (1885-1943) |work=Queen's Encyclopedia |publisher=Queen's University |accessdate=2012-10-12}}</ref>

